owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
It indicates different precision levels of the GPS coordinates obtained for a site. 
(1)CIV = the coordinates have the street civic number precision (the best situation from automatic geocoding: there is an exact matching of address and coordinates);  
(2)STR = the coordinates have the street precision (a point along the street: civic number not found); 
(3)CIT = the coordinates are relative to the city centre (street name not found); 
(4)MAN = the coordinated has been manually obtained by the user.
